Field1: Katunga Fresh Pty Ltd, a leading grower of hydroponic tomatoes, is seeking a full‐time VEGETABLE GROWER for their farm located in Katunga, Victoria. This position involves direction and oversight of general farm activities including application of fertilizers and other nutrients, pest/weed control, monitoring of the farm growing operations, production/crop production coordination and planning taking into account external factors, selecting and planting seeds, seedlings and grafting new varieties to root stocks, assisting production by de‐budding and pruning to maintain optimal growing conditions, maintaining farm buildings and related equipment and resources, and forecasting production figures and quality control. The successful candidate will have proven experience in farm techniques and farm management, will be patient, hardworking and resourceful, and will be able to work and communicate effectively as part of our dedicated and motivated growing and production team. Qualifications: This position requires at least an AQF Certificate II or III or 5 years of relevant experience
